cs.IT, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.NT, cs.SD

This paper deals with permutation functions over finite fields and their applications in constructing interleavers. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves investigating the cycle structure of these permutation functions, which falls under the category of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper uses Skolem sequences, which are commonly used in combinatorics and graph theory, falling under the category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also involves studying the properties of Mobius and Redei functions, which are related to number theory, making cs.NT (Number Theory) a likely category. Finally, the paper involves constructing new interleavers, which falls under the category of cs.SD (Systems and Control).
